com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class CreateChangeListRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianRequest
      • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.CreateChangeListRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class CreateChangeListRequest
extends SiperianRequest
    Represents a request object to create a change list in the XML format for the current Operational Reference Store (ORS). The source repository can be in the XML format or can be a respository on a physical database.

    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    API Pair: CreateChangeListResponse

    API Group: Metadata Management

      • getTransactionAttributeType

        public TransactionAttributeType getTransactionAttributeType()
        Gets the type of the transaction attribute that specifies whether this request object can participate in the transactions. Used internally by the MDM Hub to determine the transactional capabilities of a request.

        Overrides:
        getTransactionAttributeType in class SiperianRequest
        Returns:
        • NOT_SUPPORTED if the request cannot participate in the transactions.
        • SUPPORTS if the request can participate in the transactions.
        • REQUIRED if the request requires a transaction.
        • REQUIRES_NEW if the request requires a new transaction.
